data.title: Scout-O-Fair - Ft. Mott
data.meta_description:
Wally Harris winds up the rubber band engine on the wire-strung racing propeller driven "rocket" at the mini Jamboree. 
	
	I don't recall if these were supposed to be judged for speed or for distance, but I seem to recall that sanding as little as possible from the balsa wood block was actually by design, thinking that more mass would keep the item going further.
	
	I have no recollection whether or not it worked, but my suspicion is that it did not.
data.text:
Wally Harris winds up the rubber band engine on the wire-strung racing propeller driven "rocket" at the mini Jamboree.

I don't recall if these were supposed to be judged for speed or for distance, but I seem to recall that sanding as little as possible from the balsa wood block was actually by design, thinking that more mass would keep the item going further.

I have no recollection whether or not it worked, but my suspicion is that it did not.
